fields.name: Filtering experiment for shoplifting videos from YouTube
fields.description:
Thank you for joining our experiment!
In this experiment, you will be asked to watch a video from start to its ending, then please answer a set of questions at the bottom of this page.
Please do not hesitate to contact to us for further questions regarding to this experiment.

  1. Definition

Shoplifting is the act of knowingly taking goods from an establishment in which they are displayed for sale, without paying for them.

  1. Requirements

The above definition is taken from Wikipedia. It is easy to observe three important aspects of a shoplifting scene:

  • Activity: Shoplifting is an acitivity of taking something from someone or organizations.
  • Goods and shops: There must be goods which are displayed for sale in a shop (indoor or maybe outdoor in some cases).
  • No payment: The good is taken by a person from a shop without any payment. (Note that, it is OK to watching and checking the good many times, but finally making a payment. For e.g., a man who watching many goods inside the shop for 3 hours and then making a payment and obtaining a bill is NOT shoplifting. But if a man take some goods after one or two minutes, go out without paying money and obtaining a bill, that is exatly shoplifting.)

Although the above definition is strict, in practice, we may want to notice the criminals as soon as the sign of crimes appear. Therefore, some common senses can be used when you find that the above conditions are unclear to judge a crime, such as:

  • Suspicious activities: it is unusual for a person to put a good that he/she has not paid for, into his/her pocket. This situation should be put in an alarm. Justice force will decide whether to put a further investigation on the target.
  • Prank, movies, unnatural scenes: In the social networks and video sharing sites, it is usual to observe many scenes which look real but after a further investigation, it turns out that those videos are pranks. Please do not worry about those at this stage, we will ask other professionals to put their effort in further investigations.

When you find that your are in a situation which is difficult to make decisions about the crimes, please check the video as "Not Sure" and put your comments about why you were hesitating in the textbox of the final question. Some other notes:

  • Do not mark the stealing in game videos or surreal videos as positive.
  • A scene with violence but without clear evidences of shoplifting should not be checked as positive.

For a training before watching the videos, please watch the following examples:

  • Positive (shoplifting events): P1, P2
  • Negative (no shoplifting): N1, N2, N3, N4

fields.text: Did you find a shoplifting criminal in this video?
If you are hesitating about the decisions, please check "Not Sure" in the first question and put your reasons in the below box. Please be compact about the reason.
